Prophet, your words: &quot;good men in a bad war&quot; were incredibly perfect.  YES.  You all were (or most) good men/boys in a bad place.  Yes, you earned medals for individual acts of goodness, of bravery, in a bad place.  That is something to be proud of, not ashamed. When I raise questions about good medals in a bad war, it is NOT as an individual challenge, but as a more global thought.  If we can't think about all the spokes on the wheel, we are doomed to be going round and round forever, no?  I put myself in your place and learned alot about me, for better or worse, but at least it stopped my stale thinking and woke up some wrong perceptions I was holding.  Isn't that Really what this exchange is all about?<br><br>
Doc Del, as usual your post's are accurate and on the mark. I too think how America &quot;welcomed&quot; you guys home was and continues to be a disgrace. Hear that guys. Me, the resistor thinks your got a second screwing, from a stupid public who ignored you upon returning. I totally agree with your rage about that return.  If Louie Farrakan can have a million man march, why not a Viet Vet's March too?  Could be a real healing thing.<br><br>
To those who think attacking me, or sending anonomous e mails or new sites is the way to go; all I can say is I'm sorry for you. No, I take that back. Your need to hit and run is your problem to deal with.  I've heard enough personal shit as a shrink for 25 years to not want, need, desire, etc., to hear more, and for free to boot.  Go work it out somewhere else.  If you can't stand my style of thinking cause it is different than yours, To F....in bad. I happen to think that my role in the cosmos, or this site, is to spark critical thinking.  I love critical thinking and I hate bullshit stale thoughts.  But...critical thinking starts at home, and I believe I have clearly demonstrated that I learned and grew from ALL of you out there.  And I am most grateful for that...<br><br>
So, if you got something to say, Say it to my face. Either have the cajone's to post it here, with your name and e mail, or send it to my e mail privately, but for God's Sake, the hit and run artist, the punk who writes under a different name, the real coward who cuts and run, was never a veteran, or a resistor.  Remember Comrades (and comrade means comrade in arms, not some communist type), to resist means you must recognize the force that your are resisting.  I acknowledge and respect that force, of which most of you have the class to post here.<br><br>
doc<br><br>

